entries.femaleVariant: Yes, and we're closed.
Farida?
I hear you collect souvenirs from the Unification War.
Name's V.
FIA sent me.
Got somethin'... might interest you.
Name's V.
Reed and Alex sent me.
What do you want? I'm busy.
I'm sorry I was unwelcoming.
Do you know why we have rules? Procedures? To goddamn follow them.
No time to lose.
I need to prepare somehow?
I need to do anything or…?
OK, no time to lose.
OK, anesthesia incoming. Don't worry, it's the good stuff. Relax and submit.
[Sit in exam chair] Rare tech, sounds like.
To be honest... never heard of tech like this. Seems kinda… sci-fi.
entries.maleVariant: To be honest... never heard of tech like this. Seems kind of… sci-fi.

entries.femaleVariant: And do me a favor – don't tell me what you need this for.
I doubt it.
That means nothing to me.
Who the fuck are they?
Twenty questions first? Should I hold your hand?
Tush, meet chair.
[Sit in exam chair] Night City native?
[Sit in exam chair] Clinic in Dogtown? Why run it here?
So… you a Night City native?
Why run a clinic in Dogtown of all places?
OK, anesthesia's taking hold.
Thanks for everything.
Might pop by if I need anything else.
Mhm. It was picked off the corpse of a Militech R&D project.
Yet more questions... Did they tell you nothing about not delving?
The rents are low. And I siphon as much electricity as I need.
Uh-huh, right.
I can't wait.
All done. The facial morph implant is online. Now all you need is a behavioral imprint.
How many fingers 'm I holdin' up?
Thanks. For everything.
Might see me again.
I'm not taking any new customers. Sorry to inconvenience you.
They say you're a collector. Unification War-era trinkets.
Ugh...
Come in. Be quick about it.
Hear you collect trinkets – Unification War era.
Mhm... Come in.
The sooner we begin, the sooner we finish.
No. Do nothing.
Hey, Johnny.
Ugh. Fuck off.
Not now, Johnny. Fuck off, please.
Nice to see you in good form.
Ya missed me. Warms the cockles, truly.
Mhm... You want somethin' from me.
So tell me, what's it feel like to be a traitor?
Secret agent, you mean, right?
Doin' what I gotta do to survive. Figured you'd understand.
Interesting way of saying "undercover FIA agent."
Shit, actually bought into this? They send ya to a fancy party, stroke your ego, and now you're some kinda super spy?
Doin' what I need to do to survive.
You Farida?
This an FIA prototype?
Militech abandon it?
That or they sought to keep it off the books. Top secret, mum's the word.
Politics.
But... yes. I'm from Watson.
Oh, ya gotta know Viktor, then. He's a choom.
You would truly be better off keeping things like that to yourself.
Heh, can't tell if you're bein' serious.
Start your own biz in Night City proper, then come see me in a month. We'll compare accounts.
To chat. Got no other options, you'll have to do.
I got a choice?
What's next? Fuckin' gold medal, ticker tape parade? A statue? A national holiday? Kids home from school? What the fuck?!
C'mon, you know this is a lose-lose clusterfuck of a sitch. I ain't here by choice.
Oh fuck, even talkin' like they do. Just usin' different words.
"That's the job. No other way. For the greater good."
Christ, it's exactly why I ditched the ranks.
Least you see that. Means they haven't turned you yet, not completely.
C'mon, got iron in your hand. Gotta put it to someone's head, pull the trigger.
Tragedy, with me as the victim maybe?
You just don't like 'em.
The master spy and the agent unloosed. Tragedy, comedy or both?
Reed I understand, but I don't get what you have against her.
Think one of 'em's tryin' to dupe me?
No, they're both tellin' the truth. I mean, might be muddy on the nitty gritty, but their motivations are plain 'n' clear.
Survival – it's her be-all an' end-all. That and she's a walkin', talkin' nuke. The kind that keeps makin' mistakes, never knowin' which one's gonna set 'er off.
Let's just say I know where they're both comin' from.
And Reed… bastard and me are one and the same. If I hadn't ghosted the army, I'd've become a Reed myself. Live and die by our principles.
That's the tragedy, V. Someone's gonna play victim to the other's good intentions.
Hm, who would've thunk…?
Not lettin' me out of your sight.
Need to talk.
Huh. Here to see me…?
Not givin' me any breathin' room, huh? Trust an issue?
Good you're here, Reed. Need to talk, we do.
entries.maleVariant: Good you're here, Reed. Need to talk.

entries.femaleVariant: Just lookin' out.
Things're in flux, the situation's changin' fast. I thought we should talk.
But I need to help So Mi first. She's lost, and I'm concerned she doesn't know what she's doin'.
So Mi… she reached out. Wasn't tellin' the whole truth before. Wants out – off the grid.
V, good to see you.
What I don't trust is the shit from beyond the Blackwall and the attendant paranoia. Both in play here, I'm afraid.
I have something for you. Our best minds in D.C. cooked it up.
ICEbreaker. Silver bullet against any fortified netrunner. Farida'll feed it it into your system durin' surgery.
Use that, and So Mi will drop unconscious within a minute.
Has it planned for right after we take down Hansen. Gonna make a run for it, slip outta Night City.
I-- Thank you, V. For your candor.
How's it work?
Song could sense it.
She could sense the breaker. Not talkin' about some run-of-the-mill 'runner here.
Sure this soft'll work? Doubt it's been tested on anyone at Songbird's level.
OK, how do I use it?
Fire it up when you're both jacked into the mainframe. At that moment So Mi's door'll be wide open.
Hope you've got this right.
Sure hope you haven't botched this.
Two of you could just, y'know, sit down, talk it out.
You two can't just… talk?
This is gonna turn to shit.
Ugh, this'll turn to shit.
It's metaheuristic, hyper-aggressive tech. Cobbled together by a literal army of experts.
If she does sense it, it won't matter. No one out there, alone, could withstand somethin' like this.
My sentiments exactly.
Ever since a certain spaceplane crashed nearby, I've had to be more cautious.
This means a lot to me.
From what they tell me, this program can anticipate what she'll do before she even thinks to do it.
By the time you cut one thread, it's already found another. A precision-guided weapon designed to evade countermeasures.
Well, that's a hope we share, then.
Who says it has to?
Dunno, man. But say you do corner her… expect the unexpected if you know what I mean.
There comes a time when all expectations are null and void.
That's my aim, precisely.
After you… kidnap her? Not quite the same.
entries.maleVariant: After you… kidnap 'er? Not quite the same.

entries.femaleVariant: We've come to a point where some options are simply off the table.
It's time I was on my way. I leave you in Farida's able hands.
An ID modding implant is complicated tech, true, but the procedure is surprisingly simple.
Try not to forget that when you're standin' over that fuckin' overgrown neurodrive.
[Sit in exam chair] Heard of this tech.
This tech – actually heard about it. Back at Arasaka Counterintel. We thought it got the chop at the prototype stage…
As you can see, it yet lives. Chatterbox…
But seriously, found yourself in a shitastic situation.
What would you do if you were me?
You haven't been much help.
Reed or Songbird… What would you do in my shoes, Johnny?
I am in your shoes, dumbass. For every gonk choice you make. But I can't do dick.
But honest to God, V, not fuckin' around… I dunno. Got no goddamn clue.
Some help you've been…
Just don't do anything either of us'll regret later. Not you, not me.
And don't kid yourself. Both of 'em need you, but neither trusts you.
Are you still there?
Hello...? Hello?
V, all clear?
V, you can help her, and yourself.
Ahem. I don't have all day.
Sit, please.
What are you waiting for?
Heavy stuff, huh?
They're not your friends. Don't say I didn't warn ya.
Well, what now?
That's... me.
'S that... me?
I made it especially for you. I'm glad you like it.
We can't take any chances. And when she wakes up, she'll wake up at home.
But... what--?
It's facial morph technology. It needs a baseline. That baseline is you.
Stop fidgeting! You want it to be crooked?
I should have put you completely under…
I'm here about So Mi.
I spent hours... wrappin' my head around this, puttin' myself in her shoes.
I needed to understand what she musta been goin' through to… to resort to treason.
You're in no position to understand, Reed. Your life ain't on a timer.
Basin' your expectations on the woman you used to know – not on who she is today.
Nope, can't understand. You're not dyin'.
Sure you got your priorities straight?
She changed over those seven years.
Tryin' to understand 'er, really? Or just lookin' for the key to bringin' her in?
entries.maleVariant: Tryin' to understand 'er, really? Or just lookin' for the key to bringin' 'er in?

entries.femaleVariant: She's trapped. Not just here 'n' now, but goin' months back. Hell, actually years.
But I know Death. Stared him in the eyes, up close.
Common denominators remain in place.
'S no wonder So Mi doesn't trust anyone. Except maybe you, a little.
I blame Myers – a sore loser, does her damndest to avoid it. Songbird, the Blackwall… dirty tricks meant to give 'er a competitive edge.
Song should trust you – not me. That it?
Bet you wish So Mi would trust you instead.
I can't say I really blame her, can only blame myself.
Songbird's goin' to prison.
But, could you've done anything differently?
Somethin'. Anything. 'Stead of... givin' in to bein' exiled in Night City, a couple thousand miles away.
There's a prison cell prepped and waitin' for 'er already. So Mi knows that full well.
entries.maleVariant: There's a prison cell prepped and waitin' for her already. So Mi knows that full well.

entries.femaleVariant: She lives to see tomorrow and every day after – that's what matters.
You work for Myers.
So Mi tried to kill you, too.
Myers needs 'er alive, sure, but forgive and forget the attempt on her life? Never.
Myers might not forgive 'er, but… doesn't mean I can't.
What're you tryin' to bring me around to?
OK, we break the chain Hansen wrapped around her neck – then what?
Comin' from a federal agent, sayin' you want to get 'er home doesn't sound so warm 'n' fuzzy.
You forgettin'? Woman tried to zero you, too.
Whatcha tryin' to sell me, Reed?
I will get her home. Exactly how remains to be seen.
Nothin'. I'm merely tryin' to convince you.
We stow away somewhere safe, ask some questions, establish some common ground.
Once I get the answers I'm lookin' for, I'll personally help 'er disappear. From everyone everywhere. Including Myers.
That's treason.
What're you gonna ask her?
Wanna ask 'er a few questions, huh…
Y'know, some'd call that treason.
entries.maleVariant: Y'know, some would call that treason.

entries.femaleVariant: To understand her side. Got an idea already of what I'll hear. The system broke 'er, almost took her life. Like it did mine.
As for me, well… my time's well past. But So Mi's still worth savin'.
Make a good liar, Reed.
Spinnin' quite the yarn, playin' me. Fits the M.O. of someone who used to recruit spies for a livin'.
Tell me somethin' I don't know.
Fuck... no! Just listen.
I got contacts in Europe. We'll find the best clinic – put you two back together, fix what's broken. Once we have your cure in hand.
You don't trust 'er.
She has another plan in mind. I'm damn sure of it.
What's all this mean next?
She told me her plan. Intends to escape.
No, my aim is to save her.
Her hand's been forced too many times in her life. She's due compensation.
Believe you.
Say I believe you. Where's your plan go from there?
Read you loud 'n' clear… So what's it all mean next?
Call me once you're done here.
Sure it'll be enough?
Right now we're focusin' on savin' your lives. Talkin' time'll come later.
